WSL install in windos systme and ubunto os show GUI mode (install steps) without virtual box install
****************************************************************************************************
1. sudo apt update
2. sudo apt install tasksel
3. sudo tasksel 
   -> new window open then select ->KDE Plasma (space key use to select and up down arrow to move, Tab key use to ok) its install time may be 15/30 then
4. ip a (here you show ip address but you choose second 2 no ip like its start 172.... )
5. windows search panel -> then search Remote Desktop Connection -> then pase ip address -> use ubuntu user name and password)
6. After install KDE Plasma then > CMD > wsl > ip a > remote desktop (2nd ip insert)> userID: sohanur>p:8

*****************Git Cli login Command********************
1. git config --global user.name "GitHub user same name"
2. git config --global user.email "Github login Email"
3. git config --global -list

*************Git CLI***********************
1. git init                             ---git initialize 
2. git status                           ---every time check file position or status
3. git add * / git add .               --- This command use for every change when
4. git commit -m "commit here"          --- When file edit then every time commit 
-------Git locally change-----
1. git log --oneline                    ---check how many commit here
2. git reset --soft HEAD~1              ---No change code only commit delete one by one, like a queue
3. git reset --hard HEAD~1              ---commit delete with code that means back to previous version and use to top head delete
4.  git reset --hard <commit_id_here>    ---specific code commit delete with code that means back to the previous version and jump
5. git checkout <commit_id_here>        --- move to specific commit temporarily

1Ô∏è‚É£ git init
  Flag	      Meaning	                                       Example
--bare	      Create a repository without working directory	git init --bare myrepo.git
--shared	      Make repo accessible to a group	               git init --shared
2Ô∏è‚É£ git add
Flag	          Meaning	                                       Examples
-A / --all	    Add all changes (new, modified, deleted)	      git add -A
.	             Add current directory	                        git add .
-u            	 Add modified & deleted files, skip new files	git add -u
-p	             Interactively choose chunks	                  git add -p file.txt
3Ô∏è‚É£ git commit
Flag	            Meaning	                                 Example
-m "msg"	         Commit with message inline	               git commit -m "Initial commit"
-a	               Stage tracked files before commit	      git commit -a -m "Update tracked files"
--amend	         Amend last commit	git commit             --amend -m "Corrected message"
--allow-empty	   Commit even if no changes	               git commit --allow-empty -m "Empty commit"
-v	               Show diff in editor	                     git commit -v
4Ô∏è‚É£ git status
Flag	Meaning	Example
-s / --short	Short format	git status -s
-b	Show branch info	git status -b
--ignored	Show ignored files	git status --ignored
5Ô∏è‚É£ git log
Flag	Meaning	Example
--oneline	One line per commit	git log --oneline
--graph	ASCII graph of history	git log --graph
--decorate	Show branch/tag names	git log --decorate
--all	Show all branches	git log --all
-p	Show diff for each commit	git log -p
--since="2 days ago"	Filter by date	git log --since="2025-11-01"
--stat	Show summary of changed files	git log --stat
6Ô∏è‚É£ git branch
Flag	Meaning	Example
-a	Show all branches (local + remote)	git branch -a
-r	Show only remote branches	git branch -r
-d	Delete branch	git branch -d feature/ui
-D	Force delete branch	git branch -D feature/ui
-m	Rename branch	git branch -m old new
7Ô∏è‚É£ git checkout / git switch
Flag	Meaning	Example
-b <branch>	Create and switch to new branch	git checkout -b feature/api
--detach	Switch to commit, detached HEAD	git checkout --detach 8c68315
-	Switch to previous branch	git checkout -
--track <remote/branch>	Track remote branch	git checkout -b feature/ui origin/feature/ui
Modern: git switch	New way to switch branches	git switch dev
-c	Create & switch (switch alternative)	git switch -c feature/api
8Ô∏è‚É£ git push
Flag	Meaning	Example
-u / --set-upstream	Set upstream tracking	git push -u origin feature/ui
-f / --force	Force push	git push -f origin main
--all	Push all branches	git push --all origin
--tags	Push all tags	git push --tags
--dry-run	Preview push	git push --dry-run origin main
9Ô∏è‚É£ git pull
Flag	Meaning	Example
--rebase	Rebase local commits	git pull --rebase origin main
--ff-only	Only fast-forward, fail otherwise	git pull --ff-only origin main
--all	Fetch all remotes	git pull --all
üîü git reset
Flag	Meaning	Example
--soft	Reset commit history, keep changes staged	git reset --soft HEAD~1
--mixed	Reset history & staging, keep working dir	git reset --mixed HEAD~1
--hard	Reset everything	git reset --hard HEAD~1
HEAD~1	Refers to one commit before HEAD	git reset --hard HEAD~1
1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ git fetch
Flag	Meaning	Example
--all	Fetch all remotes	git fetch --all
--prune	Remove deleted remote branches locally	git fetch --prune
<remote>	Fetch from specific remote	git fetch origin
1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ git diff
Flag	Meaning	Example
--staged / --cached	Show staged changes	git diff --staged
--color-words	Show word-level diff	git diff --color-words
<file>	Show diff of a file	git diff file.txt
HEAD~1	Compare with previous commit	git diff HEAD~1

